quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,52,"But it is nothing else than a Reminder to all the ‘Âlamîn (mankind, and jinn)."
  69,49,"And verily, We know that there are some among you that belie (this Qur’ân). (Tafsir At-Tabarî)"
  69,50,"And indeed it (this Qur’ân) will be an anguish for the disbelievers (on the Day of Resurrection).{1}",footnotes:1:{69:50} See the footnote of (Verse 3:85).
  69,51,"And verily, it (this Qur’ân) is an absolute truth with certainty.{1}",footnotes:1:{69:51} See the footnote of {10:37}.
  70,43,"The Day when they will come out of the graves quickly as racing to a goal,"
  70,44,"With their eyes lowered in fear and humility, ignominy covering them (all over)! That is the Day which they were promised!"
  74,28,"It spares not (any sinner), nor does it leave (anything unburnt)!"
  74,29,"Burning and blackening the skins!"
  74,30,"Over it are nineteen (angels as guardians and keepers of Hell)."
  75,25,"Thinking that some calamity is about to fall on them."
  75,26,"Nay, when (the soul) reaches to the collar bone (i.e. up to the throat in its exit),"
  75,27,"And it will be said: "
  76,19,"And round about them will (serve) boys of everlasting youth. If you see them, you would think them scattered pearls."
  76,20,"And when you look there (in Paradise), you will see a delight (that cannot be imagined), and a great dominion."
  76,21,"Their garments will be of fine green silk, and gold embroidery. They will be adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them a pure drink."
  77,16,"Did We not destroy the ancients?"
  77,17,"So shall We make later generations to follow them."
  77,18,"Thus do We deal with the Mujrimûn (polytheists, disbelievers, sinners, criminals)."
  78,13,"And We have made (therein) a shining lamp (sun)."
  78,14,"And We have sent down from the rainy clouds abundant water."
  78,15,"That We may produce therewith corn and vegetations,"
  79,7,"The second blowing of the Trumpet follows it (and everybody will be resurrected)."
  79,8,"(Some) hearts that Day will shake with fear and anxiety."
  79,9,"Their eyes will be downcast."
  80,4,"Or he might receive admonition, and the admonition might profit him?"
  80,5,"As for him who thinks himself self-sufficient,"
  80,6,"To him you attend;"
  81,1,"When the sun is wound round and its light is lost and is overthrown.{1}",footnotes:1:{81:1} Narrated Abu Hurairah رضي الله عنه: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "The sun and the moon will be folded up (or joined together or deprived of their lights) on the Day of Resurrection." [See the Qur’ân {75:9}] (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.4, Hadith No.422).
  81,2,"And when the stars fall."
  81,3,"And when the mountains are made to pass away;"